default&#xa0;defaultQuestion 15default:default defaultW
defaulthich
default defaulthabitats do you think should be considered irreplaceable? 
default&#xa0;
defaultNo.  The importance of an irreplaceable habitat should be taken into account through the planning system and the mitigation hierarchy.  The question is the multiplier for destroying such habitats.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe suggest particular attention needs to be given to connectivity and the possibility that a habitat may have an added value because of its location. For example the value of a particular site may not be high in itself, but it may have considerable sign
defaultificance as part of a corridor. 
default&#xa0;
